text: Clayton County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 17,043. The county seat is Elkader. The county was founded in 1837 and was named in honor of John M. Clayton, United States Senator from Delaware and later Secretary of State under President Zachary Taylor. == References == Category:1837 establishments in Wisconsin Territory Category:Iowa counties
title: Clayton County, Iowa
